From f2f0afee852f8d72a8ebe0b218fa016a93b78c48 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 22:45:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Instagram owner first-comment now actually captured
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause: the comment-author match compared the owner's @handle against
yt-dlp's `author_id`, which is a numeric ID — so the owner's own comment was
always discarded even when yt-dlp returned it.

- Match on BOTH `author` (username) and `author_id` against a set of all owner
  identifiers (uploader_id, channel_id, channel, uploader, handle).
- Add instaloader fallback (_instaloader_first_owner_comment) for when yt-dlp
  returns no comments — uses the mounted session file, fully guarded.
- Add diagnostic logging so it's visible whether comments were fetched and
  whether an owner comment was found.
- formatter.py: raise Caption block limit 2000 -> 8000 chars so a full article
  pasted in the owner's comment isn't truncated.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01G3CevLYb6JPcyW363NyKGN
---
 src/extractors/instagram.py | 122 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 src/notes/formatter.py      |   8 +--
 2 files changed, 112 insertions(+), 18 deletions(-)

